raw._content: Singapore -- The Nimitz Class Aircraft Carrier USS Carl Vinson prepares to moor at the new logistics center, Changi Naval Base, outside Singapore City Aug. 29. The Changi harbor was recently expanded so it can accommodate ship sizes up to an aircraft carrier. This expansion, which began in 1998, was designed to enhance U.S.-Singapore naval operations. The deep-draft pier, built by the Singaporeans for American use, gives the U.S. Navy a carrier-berthing facility in Southeast Asia for the first time in nearly a decade. Vinson and Carrier Air Wing 11 sailors are in the midst of a six-month deployment in the Western Pacific and Persian Gulf region..(U.S. Navy Photo by Photographer's Mate Airman Jonathan Burnell)..
